===Pronunciation===
*[[IPA]]: /'bʌtən/
*{{audio|en-us-button.ogg|Audio (US)}}
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ʌtən|-ʌtən]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A [[fastener]] consisting of a [[knob]] or [[disc]] that is passed through a [[slit]] in the adjacent material.
#:''April fastened the '''buttons''' of her overcoat to keep out the wind.''
# A mechanical device meant to be [[press]]ed with a finger in order to open or close an electric circuit or to activate a mechanism.
#:''Pat pushed the '''button''' marked "shred" on the blender.''
# {{computing}} In computer software, an [[on-screen]] control that can be [[select]]ed as an [[activator]] of an attatched function.
#:''Click the '''button''' that looks like a house to return to your browser's home page.''
# A [[badge]] worn on clothes, fixed with a [[pin]] through the fabric.
#:''The politician wore a bright yellow '''button''' with the slogan "Vote Smart" emblazoned on it.''
# {{curling}} The center ([[bullseye]]) of the [[house]]. 

